 Supplier deems necessary, vary or modify the Re-Selling Price and further impose any other extra costs and charges on the Goods.<br>&nbsp;</li><li>For the avoidance of doubt, you are prohibited from selling the sold Goods to your customers or end-users at a higher or lower price from the Re-Selling Price.<br>&nbsp;</li><li>You are also fully responsible to ensure that any subsequent customers or end-users are prohibited from selling the sold Goods to their customers or end-users at a higher or lower price from the Re-Selling Price and to comply with the terms and conditions of this Agreement.<br>&nbsp;</li><li>Upon receipt of the Purchase Price (as defined below), the Supplier shall deliver the Goods ordered by you within reasonable periods at the delivery address stated in the Purchase Order.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li><li>All rights, titles, interests and risks to the Goods shall pass to you, your customers or end-users (whichever is applicable) when the Goods are deemed delivered according to the shipping terms stated in the Purchase Order.<br>&nbsp;</li><li>If the Supplier anticipates that it is unable to deliver the Goods by the delivery date stated in the Purchase Order, the Supplier shall provide a written notice to you as soon as the Supplier becomes aware of such fact. The parties agree to mutually discuss to rectify the delay of the delivery of the Goods.<br>&nbsp;</li><li>Upon delivery of the Goods, the Supplier shall allow you or your customers or end-users to inspect the Goods and you or your customers or end-users shall notify the Supplier within three (3) Business Days from the date of actual receipt of the Goods if there is any defects or shortage in quantity of the Goods. Otherwise, the Goods will be deemed accepted unconditionally by you or your customers or end-users. The Supplier will not assume any responsibility or liability for any damages or loss to the Goods resulting from any delays or events beyond its control.<br>&nbsp;</li><li>Upon the Supplier’s receipt of the documentary evidence or proof of defects and subject to the Supplier’s investigation to determine whether the said complain is meritable and further subject to the Supplier’s final decision and approval, your sole and exclusive remedy against the Supplier shall be the delivery of the shortfall and/or replacement of defective Goods (where applicable) (“<strong>Remedy</strong>”). The Supplier shall provide the Remedy within two (2) months (or any longer date to be decided by the Supplier) from the date you or your customers or end-users notify the Supplier pursuant to Clause 3.18. The Remedy shall be at your own costs and expenses, including the transportation charges, taxes and duties incurred for the delivery of the shortfall and/or replacement of the Goods. Notwithstanding this, if you otherwise provide satisfactory documentary evidence that the shortage or defective Goods is caused by the Supplier’s negligence, then the Supplier shall bear all such costs and expenses incurred by you or your customers or end-users arising from the Supplier’s negligence provided always that all such costs and expenses have been previously agreed upon by the Supplier.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li><li>No defective Goods may be returned to the Supplier without the prior written consent of the Supplier and you shall be subject to the all charges and costs in relation to the defective Goods.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li><li>In the event of any discrepancies between the terms of this Agreement, the terms of the Purchase Order, and the terms of other documents related to the subject matter of this Agreement, the terms of this Agreement shall always prevail.<br>&nbsp;</li></ol><p>&nbsp;</p><ol><li><strong>Purchase Price and Payment Term&nbsp;</strong><br>&nbsp;</li><li>The Purchase Price for the Goods are as set out in <strong>Item 2, Schedule</strong> of this Agreement.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li><li>You shall make payment of the Purchase Price prior to the delivery of the Goods.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li><li>You agree that the Supplier is entitled to, at the sole and absolute discretion of the Supplier and as the Supplier deems necessary, vary or modify the Purchase Price and further impose any other extra costs and charges on the Goods (inclusive of (without limitation) the packaging costs, insurance fees, handling fees, shipment fees and taxes).<br>&nbsp;</li></ol><p>&nbsp;</p><ol><li><strong>Warranties And Representations</strong><br>&nbsp;</li><li>You hereby warrant and represent to each other that:<br>&nbsp;</li><li>if you are a corporation, you are a corporation duly organised and validly existing under the laws of the jurisdiction of its organisation or incorporation and you have obtained all consents required and all internal approvals (including board of directors’ approval and shareholders’ approval, if required) for the entry into this Agreement;<br>&nbsp;</li><li>you have the legal right and full capacity, power and corporate authorisations to enter into and perform and bind itself by this Agreement;<br>&nbsp;</li><li>the signing of this Agreement and the performance of its obligations under this Agreement will not result in a breach or termination of any other agreement or arrangement to which you are a party;<br>&nbsp;</li><li>you are not insolvent and will not become insolvent as a result of entering into this Agreement;<br>&nbsp;</li><li>you have not presented nor received any petition, application or other proceedings for bankruptcy / winding up or administration, creditors’ voluntary arrangement or similar relief by which the affairs, businesses or assets of the party concerned;<br>&nbsp;</li><li>you have not involved in any current or pending investigations, actions, suits or proceedings;&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li><li>no bribery, corruption, unlawful or illegal activities or practices have been used to secure or otherwise enter into this Agreement; and<br>&nbsp;</li><li>you are in compliance and will comply with all laws applicable to you.<br>&nbsp;</li><li>In addition to Clause 5.1, you further irrevocably and unconditionally undertake, represent and warrants to the Supplier that:<br>&nbsp;</li><li>you shall strictly comply with all the terms and conditions of this Agreement and the Purchase Order, including your payment obligations to the Supplier; and&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li><li>you shall strictly comply with all directions and instructions of the Supplier and the rules, regulations, manuals, memos and/or guidelines imposed by the Supplier from time to time in connection with this Agreement and the Purchase Order; and&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li><li>you shall use your best endeavors and efforts to protect the interests and reputation of the Supplier and the brand of the Goods.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li><li>Save for those provided under this Agreement, the Supplier does not make and hereby disclaims all representations or warranties of any kind, express or implied, including (a) the implied warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, title, and non-infringement; (b) that the Goods will meet yours and/or your customers and/or your end-users’ requirements.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li><li>You shall assist your team members (as stated in the Systems) (“<strong>Team Members</strong>”) to complete the relevant registration in the Systems. You must witness the acceptance of this Agreement by all your Team Members. You must also provide all the necessary training and guidance for all your team members as and when it is required.<br>&nbsp;</li><li>Clauses 5.2 and 5.3 hereof shall continue to survive notwithstanding the expiry or termination of this Agreement.<br>&nbsp;</li></ol><p>&nbsp;</p><ol><li><strong>Indemnity</strong><br>&nbsp;</li><li>You hereby covenant and agree that you shall fully indemnify the Supplier against all claims of any kind or nature whatsoever, costs, expenses, losses, damages or liabilities sustained by the Supplier as a result of any breach of the warranties, representations, covenants, terms and conditions of this Agreement by you.<br>&nbsp;</li><li>In no event shall the Supplier be liable to you and/or your customer and/or your end-user for any incidental, or consequential loss of any kind, indirect, punitive or special damages of any kind, including without limitation, loss of profits or savings, loss of business or revenues, loss of goodwill or business interruption, whether foreseeable or not, and whether arising from breach of this Agreement or otherwise.<br>&nbsp;</li><li>Clause 6 shall continue to survive notwithstanding the expiry or termination of this Agreement.<br>&nbsp;</li></ol><p>&nbsp;</p><ol><li><strong>Duration and Termination&nbsp;</strong><br>&nbsp;</li><li>This Agreement shall be valid and enforceable with immediate effect from the date of acceptance of this Agreement by you for the Term of the Agreement, unless otherwise terminated in accordance with the terms of this Agreement.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li><li>Without prejudice to the rights and remedies available to the Supplier under this Agreement, the Supplier is entitled to rightfully terminate this Agreement under the following situations:-<br>&nbsp;</li><li>where you breach any of the terms and conditions under this Agreement or the Purchase Order and fail to remedy such breaches within fourteen (14) days from the date the Supplier notifies you of the breaches;<br>&nbsp;</li><li>where you breach any of the directions, instructions, rules, regulations, manuals, memos, and/or guidelines imposed by the Supplier and fail to remedy such breaches within fourteen (14) days from the date the Supplier notifies you of the breaches;<br>&nbsp;</li><li>where you terminate this Agreement before the expiry of the Term;<br>&nbsp;</li><li>where you, in the reasonable opinion of the Supplier, is unable to fulfil your duties and obligations under this Agreement;<br>&nbsp;</li><li>you are or become insolvent or bankrupt or is subject to any winding-up petition or arrangement with its creditors; and/or&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li><li>where you have committed any act or things which brings the Supplier into disrepute or which in the Supplier’s opinion is prejudicial to the Supplier’s interests and/or reputation.<br>&nbsp;</li><li>Upon termination of this Agreement under Clause 7.2, and without prejudice to any rights that have accrued under this Agreement and the Purchase Order or any of its rights or remedies available to the Supplier:-<br>&nbsp;</li><li>the Supplier shall cease the supply of the Goods immediately;<br>&nbsp;</li><li>for the remaining points in the Systems as at the date of the termination (“<strong>Remaining Points</strong>”), all such Remaining Points shall be automatically cancelled and forfeited immediately and the Supplier is not required to pay or compensate you for any amount. In the event where you have in possession the remaining Goods which have not been sold by you and/or your customer and/or your end-user as at the date of the termination (“<strong>Unsold Goods</strong>”), you are required, at your own costs and expenses, to return the Unsold Goods to the Supplier in accordance with the Supplier’s directions and instructions and the Supplier is entitled to dispose of the Unsold Goods at any terms and conditions without reference to you and the Supplier is not required to pay or compensate you for any amount;&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li><li>the Deposit shall be forfeited by the Supplier absolutely;<br>&nbsp;</li><li>you shall pay to the Supplier a compensation sum of RM18,000.00 as agreed liquidated damages;<br>&nbsp;</li><li>you shall pay to the Supplier all monies due and owing to the Supplier under this Agreement and Purchase Order(s) up to the date of termination, including all monies owing to the Supplier under Clause 7.3(d); and<br>&nbsp;</li><li>you shall return to the Supplier any confidential information of the Supplier, if applicable.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li><li>Following the termination or expiry of this Agreement, neither of the parties will have any further rights or obligations under this Agreement to the other party except in respect of:<br>&nbsp;</li><li>any rights or obligations under this Agreement which are expressed to apply or continue to be binding after the termination or expiry of this Agreement; and<br>&nbsp;</li><li>any rights of obligations which have accrued in respect of any act, omission, or breach of any of the provisions of this Agreement to any party prior to or by virtue of such termination or expiry of the Agreement.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li><li>Clause 7 hereof shall continue to survive notwithstanding the expiry or termination of this Agreement.<br>&nbsp;</li></ol><p>&nbsp;</p><ol><li><strong>Force Majeure</strong><br>&nbsp;</li><li>If a force majeure event (including without limitation, wars, terrorism, acts of God, pandemic, epidemic, lockdowns, movement control order, emergencies, natural catastrophes, political or economic disruptions, any delay by the government authority in Malaysia and any other acts which are beyond the control of the parties) occurs and as a result the affected party is unable to perform its obligations under this Agreement, such obligations (save and except your obligation to pay the Purchase Price) will be suspended during the period of delay caused by the force majeure event and will be automatically extended by that period, and the affected party will not be subject to any penalty.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li><li>The affected party who is claiming that a force majeure event has occurred shall notify the other party immediately.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li><li>Upon cessation of the force majeure event, the parties shall continue to be bound by the terms of this Agreement.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li></ol><p>&nbsp;</p><ol><li><strong>Covenants</strong><br>&nbsp;</li><li>Unless otherwise required by law or court order, you agree that you will not divulge or disclose to any person any trade secret, strategy, materials, affairs, information, documents or any other confidential information concerning the Goods, this Agreement and/or any of our mark/logo/trademark (whether registered or unregistered) (“<strong>Marks</strong>”), which may come to your knowledge during the duration of this Agreement.<br>&nbsp;</li></ol><p>&nbsp;</p><ol><li>You agree that:-<br>&nbsp;</li><li>you recognise and acknowledge our title to the Marks and you shall not, at any time, represent to any person that you have any title, interest or right of ownership to the Marks; and<br>&nbsp;</li></ol><p>&nbsp;</p><ol><li>you agree that the use of Marks and any reputation and/or goodwill generated by you in relation to the use of the Marks pursuant to this Agreement will be accrued solely for the benefit of the Supplier.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li></ol><p>&nbsp;</p><ol><li>You hereby allow the Supplier to inspect any of your workplace or location of which you have occupied for the purposes of carrying out the sale of the Goods by you, your account books and other of your documents at any time to ensure that you have complied with the terms of this Agreement and/or you have acted in accordance with all the directions, instruction, instructions, rules, regulations, manuals, memos, and/or guidelines imposed by the Supplier from time to time.<br>&nbsp;</li><li>You irrevocably and unconditional agree and consent that the Supplier is entitled, at the sole and absolute discretion of the Supplier and as the Supplier deems necessary, to decide whether to grant any promotional package, benefits and/or incentive (“<strong>Incentive</strong>”) to you. The Supplier is entitled to vary, change, modify, amend and/or cancel the Incentive at any time without reference to you.<br>&nbsp;</li><li>Clause 9 hereof shall continue to survive notwithstanding the expiry or termination of this Agreement.<br>&nbsp;</li></ol><p>&nbsp;</p><ol><li><strong>Governing Law&nbsp;</strong><br>&nbsp;</li></ol><p>This Agreement and the Purchase Order shall be governed and construed in all respect in accordance with the laws of Malaysia and the parties hereto shall submit to the exclusive jurisdiction of the Malaysian courts.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><ol><li><strong>Personal Data Protection</strong><br>&nbsp;</li></ol><p>“Personal Data” means personal data as defined under the Personal Data Protection Act 2010 of Malaysia. You hereby give your express consent to the Supplier to (a) collect, obtain, store and process your Personal Data pursuant to this Agreement; and (b) disclose your Personal Data to third parties including relevant governmental authorities, only where required by the law or necessary for the performance of this Agreement. Where required by the Supplier, you also agree to execute a separate agreement or document governing the protection and disclosure of Personal Data between the parties.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><ol><li><strong>Cancellation of Previous Supply of Goods Agreement</strong><br>&nbsp;</li></ol><p>Upon your acceptance of this Agreement:-</p><ol><li>any existing or previous supply of goods agreement entered into between you and the Supplier (if any), purchase order (if any) and other similar documents shall be terminated, cancelled and superseded automatically with immediate effect and shall also cease to have any further legal effect immediately; and<br>&nbsp;</li><li>you shall then be immediately bound by all the terms and conditions of this Agreement.<br>&nbsp;</li></ol><p>&nbsp;</p><ol><li><strong>Others</strong><br>&nbsp;</li><li>Time whenever mentioned in this Agreement and the Purchase Order shall be of the essence.<br>&nbsp;</li><li>This Agreement and the Purchase Orders issued under this Agreement set out the entire agreement and understanding between the parties hereto as to the subject matter hereof and supersedes all prior agreement(s) (whether oral or written) between them whether express or implied.<br>&nbsp;</li><li>This Agreement shall be binding on and inure for the benefit of the respective heirs, personal representatives, successors-in-title and permitted assigns of the parties hereto.<br>&nbsp;</li><li>All rights and/or obligations hereunder are personal to the parties hereto and no party hereto shall assign or attempt to assign any such rights or obligations without the prior written consent of the other party.<br>&nbsp;</li><li>Each of the provisions of this Agreement and the Purchase Order is severable and distinct from the others and if any time one or more of such provision is or become invalid, void, illegal or unenforceable, the effectiveness and validity of the remaining clauses of this Agreement and the Purchase Order shall in no way be affected.<br>&nbsp;</li><li>The parties agree that:-<br>&nbsp;</li><li>waiver of any breach of this Agreement or of any right, power, authority, discretion or remedy arising upon a breach of or default under this Agreement, must be in writing and signed by the party granting the waiver;<br>&nbsp;</li><li>no failure on the part of a party to exercise, and no delay on its part in exercising any right or remedy under this Agreement shall operate as a waiver thereof, nor will any single or partial exercise of any right or remedy preclude any other or further exercise thereof or the exercise of any other right or remedy; and&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li><li>the rights and remedies provided in this Agreement are cumulative and not exclusive of any rights or remedies (whether provided by law or otherwise).<br>&nbsp;</li><li>No amendment, modification or variation of this Agreement shall be effective unless in writing and signed by both the parties.<br>&nbsp;</li><li>Any notice or other communication (including any request, demand, consent or approval) (a “<strong>Notice</strong>”) in connection with this Agreement or the Purchase Order:<br>&nbsp;</li><li>must be in legible writing and in the English language or such other language as the parties agree to use; and<br>&nbsp;</li><li>shall be deemed to be sufficiently given or served and deemed to be received by the addressee:<br>&nbsp;</li><li>if sent by delivery in person, when delivered to the addressee;<br>&nbsp;</li><li>if sent by registered post, three (3) Business Days after posting;&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li><li>if sent by electronic mail or through the internet or any electronic medium selected by the Supplier, immediately on dispatch.<br>&nbsp;</li><li>You shall be responsible for and shall pay all stamp duty payable on this Agreement together with any penalty payable in connection thereto, as and when the same is required to be stamped.<br>&nbsp;</li></ol><p><i>[the rest of the page is intentionally left blank]</i></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>SCHEDULE</strong></p><p><strong>(</strong><i><strong>To be construed as an integral part of this Agreement)</strong></i></p><figure class="table"><table><tbody><tr><td><strong>NO.</strong></td><td><strong>ITEM</strong></td><td><strong>DETAILS</strong></td></tr><tr><td>1.</td><td>Supervisor</td><td><p>Means the supervisor(s) appointed by the Supplier as set out in the Systems.</p><p>You agree that the Supervisor may be added on or removed at the sole and absolute discretion of the Supplier and as the Supplier deems necessary at any time.</p></td></tr><tr><td>2.</td><td>Purchase Price</td><td><p>Means the Purchase Price of the Goods as set out in the Systems.&nbsp;</p><p>You agree that the Supplier is entitled to, at the sole and absolute discretion of the Supplier and as the Supplier deems necessary, vary or modify the Purchase Price and further impose any other extra costs and charges on the Goods (inclusive of (without limitation) the packaging costs, insurance fees, handling fees, shipment fees and taxes).</p></td></tr><tr><td>3.</td><td>Re-Selling Price</td><td><p>Means the Re-Selling Price of the Goods as set out in the Systems.</p><p>You agree that the Supplier is entitled to, at the sole and absolute discretion of the Supplier and as the Supplier deems necessary, vary or modify the Re-Selling Price and further impose any other extra costs and charges on the Goods.</p></td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p><i>[the rest of the page is intentionally left blank]</i></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><i>Version: 1 – 2021</i></p>',
